On the other hand we are told that our Epistle was rejected by Theodore of Mopsuestia (d. 4029).3

Towards the end of the fourth century Jerome (representing the views of the Church of Rome) and Augustine (representing the Church of Carthage) pronounced in favour of our present Canon. The judgment of the former is given in the Vulgate and in the catalogue contained in his epistle Ad Paulinum liii. 83 elsewhere speaking of James he says (Vir.
